The paper discusses learning temporally extended actions for continuous tasks using the options framework and reinforcement learning techniques. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of the option-critic architecture and proximal policy optimization suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the results on Mujoco domains suggest a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
